result.execSummary:
The defendant Amy J Rudnitzki was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Contempt/Ct-Nonsummary/Punitive Sanction, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 785.03(1)(b).
  • Contempt/Ct-Nonsummary/Punitive Sanction, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 785.03(1)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

11:55 a.m.  Defendant present in court with Atty John Selsing.  Lisa Vanden Branden for the State of Wisconsin.  ADA recites agreement - will amend to 2 counts of criminal contempt of court in violation of 785.03(1)(b).  Atty Selsing concurs.  Defendant concurs.  ADA confirms compliance with victim witness rights.

Court goes over plea questionnaire with the defendant.  Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - defendant waives these rights.  Court goes over the elements of each offense.  Court instructs defendant of the maximum penalty.  Court instructs defendant regarding deportation. 

Defendant enters a plea of NO CONTEST.  Court finds the plea is made freely, voluntarily, intelligently and understandingly.  Court finds there is a factual basis to support the plea.  Court finds the defendant guilty on both counts on the amended counts.  Court orders the judgment of conviction be entered here today.  Statement by Thomas Yancy.  Sentencing statement by ADA.  Sentencing argument by Atty Selsing.  Statement by the defendant.

Court sentences the defendant to:  SWD, and places the defendant on probation for 24 months.

CONDITIONS:

-Comply with all of the family court orders
-NO Contact with the custodial parent except thru the family wizard program
-Defendant is to abide by all rules and recommendations of the supervising agent.
-Court costs.
